Description

The AuthToken class represents the data that is stored in the auth_token table.

ClearRequest
Empty ClearRequest body
ClearResponse
ClearResponse object holds the data for the response to a ClearRequest
ClearService
Clears all data from all tables in the database
Event
The Event class represents the data that is stored in the event table.
eventDAO
EventDAO accesses data in the database
EventRequest
The EventRequest object holds the information needed to request a specific event or all events
EventResponse
EventResponse holds the message and success status
EventService
EventService class receives an EventRequest from the EventHandler A specific event or all events are returned
FillRequest
FillRequest object holds the information that is needed to fill person data for a specified number of generations
FillResponse
FillResponse object holds data for a response to a fill operation
FillService
FillService receives a FillRequest from the handler and returns a FillResponse
LoadRequest
Clears all data from the database Loads the user, person, and event data from the request body into the database
LoadResponse
Holds the response data that will be returned with the result of the operation
LoadService
LoadService receives a request from the handler and loads the data into the database.
LoginRequest
LoginRequest object holds the information that is needed to log in a user
LoginResponse
LoginResponse holds the data and success status returned after a login is performed
LoginService
LoginService receives a LoginRequest from the handler Returns a response containing the authtoken of the new user
Person
The Person class represents the data that is stored in the person table It contains a personID, associatedUsername, firstName, lastName, gender, fatherID, motherID, spouseID Each person is connected to a user through the associatedUsername attribute This class contains getter and setter methods for each attribute
personDAO
personDAO accesses data in the database
PersonRequest
PersonRequest object for requesting a specific person or all persons connected to the current user
PersonResponse
PersonResponse holds the data that is returned to the handler after a person request is made.
PersonService
Receives a PersonRequest from the handler and returns a PersonResponse
RegisterRequest
The RegisterRequest object holds the information that is needed to register a user
RegisterResponse
RegisterResponse holds the data and success status returned after a register is performed
RegisterService
RegisterService receives a RegisterRequest from the handler Returns a response containing the authtoken of the new user
ServerTest
This is a mock client used for pass off of the CS240 Family Map Server project.
User
The User class represents data that is stored in the user table It contains a username, password, email, firstName, lastName, gender, personID The user is connected to a person in the database through the personID attribute This class contains getter and setter methods for each attribute
userDAO
userDAO accesses data in the database
